title: Hannah Brown Is Clearly a ‘Dancing with the Stars’ Front-Runner After Her Premiere Performance
text:
Looks like Hannah Brown can officially add dancing the cha-cha to her list of many talents. The Bachelorette alum showed off all of her moves during the season premiere of Dancing with the Stars last night.

The reality star and her partner Alan Bersten performed their rendition of the cha-cha to Whitney Houston’s "I Wanna Dance with Somebody."

Brown quickly wowed the judges and audience with her performance—and did we mention that split?!—which helped her earn one of the highest scores of the night.

And can we talk about that Chris Harrison appearance? In the words of the man himself, “Don’t break a leg.”

The 24-year-old announced she was joining the cast of DWTS season 28 late last month. “I am so excited,” she stated. “I want a fresh start, something that I can go all in with, emotionally, physically, spiritually, and I think dancing is something that I can do that with.”

Way to go, Hannah! We can’t wait to see what this season has in store for you.
